Just trying to understand how the graph looks like in V3Order, I have the simple test case:

module DUT (clk, in1, out);
input clk, in1;
output out;
reg out;
   always @(posedge clk) out <= in1;
endmodule

On the bottom left of the attached picture, TOP->in1 has PRE and POST are output of the yellow "ALWAYS". This is one that is not easily understood. Shouldn't TOP->in1 as input to the "ALWAYS"? 

And what "PORD" stands for?

Thanks a lot,
 

